<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-19T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="1108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/9986:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé to the Norwegian Government in
                                    Exile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-19T20:00:00+01:00">January 19, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2. Norwegian Series. Your 3, January 8, 4 p.m. Foreign Minister Lie
                                was advised on January 12 of our position regarding non-reversal of
                                earlier decision in Norsk Hydro case.</p>
                            <p>After consultation with EWD<note n="5" xml:id="d1108fn5">Economic
                                    Warfare Division in the Embassy at London.</note> which in turn
                                has consulted MEW<note n="6" xml:id="d1108fn6">Ministry of Economic
                                    Warfare.</note> (Dingle Foot<note n="7" xml:id="d1108fn7">Parliamentary Secretary to the British Ministry of Economic
                                    Warfare, 1940–45.</note>) I am refraining from informing
                                Norwegians of our detailed objections to the transaction, believing
                                it inadvisable to open up a discussion at this time.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>